# sdkconfig.qemu.defaults — layered on top of sdkconfig.defaults (and,
# for the tests/qemu/ suite, sdkconfig.selftest.defaults too) for QEMU
# builds only. See conftest.py's build_selftest_firmware, which passes all
# three via -D SDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS.
#
# CONFIG_GLOW_SKIP_WIFI is a general-purpose option (see
# firmware/main/Kconfig.projbuild's help text -- it's also useful on real
# hardware for a purely local DMX/Fennel rig with no network at all), not
# QEMU-specific by itself. It is required here because this QEMU fork has
# no WiFi/802.11 hardware model: esp_wifi_init()'s RF calibration step
# hangs forever waiting on radio status bits emulated silicon never sets,
# which otherwise stalls app_main() before DMX/Lua/the render task ever
# come up. See tests/qemu/README.md.
CONFIG_GLOW_SKIP_WIFI=y
